abstract: The results of British elections are positive in the short term as they eliminate uncertainty regarding Britain's exit process from the European Union, the European Central Bank's Vice-president Luis de Guindos said on Friday.
snippet: The results of British elections are positive in the short term as they eliminate uncertainty regarding Britain's exit process from the European Union, the European Central Bank's Vice-president Luis de Guindos said on Friday.
lead_paragraph: MADRID — The results of British elections are positive in the short term as they eliminate uncertainty regarding Britain's exit process from the European Union, the European Central Bank's Vice-president Luis de Guindos said on Friday.
headline_main: British Election Results Are Positive in Short-Term, ECB's De Guindos Says
headline_print_headline: British Election Results Are Positive in Short-Term, ECB's De Guindos Says

abstract: BEIJING — China's foreign minister on Friday labeled the United States the “troublemaker of the world," citing the Trump administration's withdrawal from a number of international treaties.
lead_paragraph: BEIJING — China's foreign minister on Friday labeled the United States the “troublemaker of the world," citing the Trump administration's withdrawal from a number of international treaties.
headline_main: China Foreign Minister Calls US 'Troublemaker of the World'
headline_print_headline: China Foreign Minister Calls US 'Troublemaker of the World'

abstract: The election result was hailed as a victory for English, Scottish and Irish nationalism - and it could spell the end of the United Kingdom.

lead_paragraph: BELFAST/GLASGOW — The election result was hailed as a victory for English, Scottish and Irish nationalism - and it could spell the end of the United Kingdom.
headline_main: Victory for Nationalism: Johnson's Win Puts UK's Future in Doubt
headline_print_headline: Victory for Nationalism: Johnson's Win Puts UK's Future in Doubt

abstract: Sterling was well supported on Friday as investors rushed to unwind bets on a weaker pound after a resounding election victory for Prime Minister Boris Johnson's Conservative Party.
snippet: Sterling was well supported on Friday as investors rushed to unwind bets on a weaker pound after a resounding election victory for Prime Minister Boris Johnson's Conservative Party.
lead_paragraph: LONDON — Sterling was well supported on Friday as investors rushed to unwind bets on a weaker pound after a resounding election victory for Prime Minister Boris Johnson's Conservative Party.
headline_main: Investors Slash Bets on Weaker Pound After Johnson's Thumping Election Win
headline_print_headline: Investors Slash Bets on Weaker Pound After Johnson's Thumping Election Win

abstract: Oil rose on Friday to its highest in nearly three months as investors cheered progress in resolving the U.S.-China trade dispute and a decisive general election result in Britain.
snippet: Oil rose on Friday to its highest in nearly three months as investors cheered progress in resolving the U.S.-China trade dispute and a decisive general election result in Britain.
lead_paragraph: NEW YORK — Oil rose on Friday to its highest in nearly three months as investors cheered progress in resolving the U.S.-China trade dispute and a decisive general election result in Britain.
headline_main: Oil Nears Three-Month High as Trade Hopes, UK Election Boost Sentiment
headline_print_headline: Oil Nears Three-Month High as Trade Hopes, UK Election Boost Sentiment

abstract: European Union leaders on Friday congratulated British Prime Minister Boris Johnson on his sweeping election victory amid optimism that his clear majority should finally allow him to push the long-stalled Brexit divorce deal through a reluctant parliament and end years of political wrangling.
snippet: European Union leaders on Friday congratulated British Prime Minister Boris Johnson on his sweeping election victory amid optimism that his clear majority should finally allow him to push the long-stalled Brexit divorce deal through a reluctant pa...
lead_paragraph: BRUSSELS — European Union leaders on Friday congratulated British Prime Minister Boris Johnson on his sweeping election victory amid optimism that his clear majority should finally allow him to push the long-stalled Brexit divorce deal through a reluctant parliament and end years of political wrangling.
headline_main: EU Relief as UK Polls Signal Brexit May Soon Be Done
headline_print_headline: EU Relief as UK Polls Signal Brexit May Soon Be Done

abstract: As President Recep Tayyip Erdogan’s popularity sinks along with the economy, onetime allies are trying to lure his supporters.
snippet: As President Recep Tayyip Erdogan’s popularity sinks along with the economy, onetime allies are trying to lure his supporters.
lead_paragraph: ANKARA, Turkey — A former prime minister and erstwhile ally of President Recep Tayyip Erdogan said on Friday that he was creating a new political party, a challenge that could splinter the governing party and fatally damage the Turkish leader’s chances for re-election.

abstract: Prime Minister Boris Johnson said a sweeping victory gives him “an overwhelming mandate” to complete Brexit, but also talked about big spending plans.
snippet: Prime Minister Boris Johnson said a sweeping victory gives him “an overwhelming mandate” to complete Brexit, but also talked about big spending plans.
lead_paragraph: Brexit will happen, Prime Minister Boris Johnson vowed as he started his postelection era, adding that improving public health care was the nation’s top priority.

abstract: Thai opposition party leader Thanathorn Juangroongruangkit called on supporters to mobilize in Bangkok on Saturday, days after the national election body called for the dissolution of his party.
snippet: Thai opposition party leader Thanathorn Juangroongruangkit called on supporters to mobilize in Bangkok on Saturday, days after the national election body called for the dissolution of his party.
lead_paragraph: BANGKOK — Thai opposition party leader Thanathorn Juangroongruangkit called on supporters to mobilize in Bangkok on Saturday, days after the national election body called for the dissolution of his party.
